Furber, Appellant, v. McCarthy, Respondent. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. March 29, 1889.) Motion to dismiss for failure to prosecute appeal.

Argued before Van Brunt, P. J., and Bartlett, J.

H. Joseph, for appellant. E. P. Johnson, for respondent.

No opinion. Motion denied, on appellants’ paying $10, costs of motion, ■and stipulating to argue at next term of the court. See 4 N. Y. Supp. 274.
